rComments: Was not the best prof. I attended Maltais' section as well as going to Devin's, and only after seeing the material once beforehand with Maltais was I able to follow along in Devin's class. Her handwriting isn't the best, with r. n, m, and pi all looking the same. She wrote the final for Winter 2018 and screwed everyone over.

It's a tough course and the prof certainly didn't help. Her lectures were long, boring and useless, I ended up learning everything online. Both midterms were extremely hard, she curved the second one because the average was so low. Final was brutal, but I can't blame that on her. Do 1000s of practice questions and past exams if you want to succeed.

I felt she was trying her best, but the truth is that the lectures were quite bad: she'd write a theorem or formula in the board, talk a bit about it (without explaining anything in detail), do one example and move to the next topic. Only take this prof. if you can learn by yourself.
Tries her best to make the content easy. Make sure to practice and pay attention in class.

I hated every minute of this class not because of the content but because of this prof. She could not simplify anything if you did not understand something. Her exams where crazy hard and she told me she makes them extra long to adjust the marks after. Our first midterm more than half the class failed. Our final was written by another professor.

She is a new prof at the school, but she's one of the best math profs I've had. Lectures are easy to follow and her notes are great. The first midterm was too hard so she apologized and made the second one much easier. Gave a lot of bonus marks on the second midterm and on quizzes to make up for it. Final was more than fair. Would highly recommend
